This presidential memorandum, issued on May 20, 2020, focuses on providing continued federal support for governors' use of the National Guard to respond to COVID-19 and facilitate economic recovery. The memorandum emphasizes the need for close cooperation and assistance between the federal government and the states in combating the threat of the virus. The actions outlined in the memorandum include directing the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to fund 100% of the emergency assistance activities associated with preventing, mitigating, and responding to the virus in Utah, using its National Guard forces. It also directs the Secretary of Defense to request the Governor of Utah to order National Guard forces to perform duty on a reimbursable basis to support state and local emergency assistance efforts. The memorandum specifies that the 100% federal cost share for Utah's use of National Guard forces will be available until June 24, 2020, and includes duty necessary to comply with health protection protocols recommended by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention or other agreed-upon health protection measures. The memorandum also includes general provisions stating that it does not impair the authority granted to executive departments or agencies and must be implemented in accordance with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations.